'''Ruben Fritzner Providence''' (born 7 July 2001) is a professional [[association football|footballer]] who plays as a [[winger (association football)|winger]] or [[forward (association football)|forward]] for Dutch {{Dutch football updater|Almere}} club [[Almere City FC|Almere City]]. Born in France, he plays for the [[Haiti national football team|Haiti national team]].

==Career==
In 2019, Providence joined the youth academy of Italian [[Serie A]] side [[A.S. Roma|Roma]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.lestitisdupsg.fr/a-la-une/news-anciens-ruben-providence-as-roma-ita-thiago-motta-ma-permis-de-me-redecouvrir/|title=[News-Anciens] Ruben Providence (AS Roma/Ita) : " Thiago Motta m'a permis de me redécouvrir ! "|date=9 April 2020|website=Les Titis du PSG}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.goal.com/fr/news/portrait-ruben-providence-le-petit-joyau-parisien/1ptwvnx1n859s1rw0a38acjway|title=Ruben Providence, le petit joyau parisien|publisher=goal.com}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.siamolaroma.it/2019/07/28/lidentikit-ecco-ruben-providence-il-secondo-gioiello-di-lagny-sur-marne-video/|title=L'Identikit, ecco Ruben Providence: il secondo gioiello di Lagny-sur-Marne (VIDEO)|first=Andrea Di|last=Carlo|date=28 July 2019}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.gazzettaregionale.it/primavera-e-berretti/2020/03/23/news/roma-ruben-providence-la-stella-spenta-di-alberto-de-rossi-95490/|title=Ruben Providence: la stella spenta di Alberto De Rossi|publisher=gazzettaregionale.it}}</ref> In 2021, he was sent on loan to [[Club Brugge KV|Club Brugge]] in Belgium.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.dhnet.be/sports/football/division-1a/fc-bruges/2021/08/28/le-pere-de-ruben-providence-presente-son-fils-le-nouveau-transfert-de-bruges-thiago-motta-laissait-ruben-sexprimer-offensivement-HGPNSKWAMVEO3AJES2D763M2QA/|title=Le père de Ruben Providence présente son fils, le nouveau transfert de Bruges: "Thiago Motta laissait Ruben s'exprimer offensivement"|publisher=dhnet.be}}</ref> Before the second half of 2021–22, he was sent on loan to Portuguese club [[G.D. Estoril Praia|Estoril]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.record.pt/futebol/futebol-nacional/liga-bwin/estoril/detalhe/ruben-providence-chega-por-emprestimo-da-roma|title=Ruben Providence chega por empréstimo da Roma|publisher=record.pt}}</ref>

In 2022, Providence was sent on loan to [[TSV Hartberg]] in Austria.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.skysportaustria.at/hartberg-praesentiert-drei-neuzugaenge/|title=Hartberg präsentiert drei Neuzugänge|publisher=skysportaustria.at}}</ref> On 2 October 2022, he debuted for TSV Hartberg during a 3–2 loss to [[SK Austria Klagenfurt (2007)|Austria Klagenfurt]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.krone.at/2820493|title=Klagenfurt-Sieg in Hartberg dank Last-Minute-Elfer|publisher=krone.at}}</ref>

On 3 August 2024, Providence featured as a trialist for [[Swansea City A.F.C.|Swansea City]] in a friendly against [[Rio Ave F.C.|Rio Ave]], where he would provide an assist.<ref>{{cite news |title=Swansea City see off Rio Ave 3-0 in pre-season |url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/articles/cx022xyveepo |access-date=29 June 2025 |publisher=BBC Sport |date=3 August 2024}}</ref> On 29 August 2024, Providence signed a three-year contract with [[Almere City FC|Almere City]] in the Netherlands.<ref>{{cite web|publisher=Almere City|url=https://almerecity.nl/almere-city-1/franse-vleugelspeler-ruben-providence-tekent-in-almere/|title=Franse vleugelspeler Ruben Providence tekent in Almer|trans-title=French winger Ruben Providence signs in Almere|date=29 August 2024|access-date=29 August 2024|language=nl}}</ref>

==Personal life==
Born in France, Providence is of Haitian and Lao descent.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://sportpassioninfo.com/foot-analyse-y-a-t-il-des-joueurs-qui-ont-peur-de-perdre-leur-place-en-equipe-nationale/|title=Foot-analyse : Y-a-t-il des joueurs qui ont peur de perdre leur place en équipe nationale ? - SPI|date=14 September 2023|website=sportpassioninfo.com}}</ref> He is a youth international for France, having played for the [[France national under-19 football team|France U19]]s.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.lesoir.be/390483/article/2021-08-20/d1a-le-club-bruges-annonce-son-deuxieme-transfert-de-la-journee|title=D1A: le Club Bruges a annoncé son deuxième transfert de la journée|date=20 August 2021|website=Le Soir}}</ref> In March 2025, he was called up to the [[Haiti national football team|Haiti national team]] for a set of friendlies.<ref>{{Cite web |last=Lagerburg |first=Jos |title=Providence debuteert in selectie Haïti, nóg vier spelers op reis - Almere City FC |url=https://almerecity.nl/almere-city-1/providence-debuteert-in-selectie-haiti-nog-zes-spelers-op-reis/ |archive-url=http://web.archive.org/web/20250329183742/https://almerecity.nl/almere-city-1/providence-debuteert-in-selectie-haiti-nog-zes-spelers-op-reis/ |archive-date=29 March 2025 |access-date=13 January 2026 |website=almerecity.nl |language=nl-NL}}</ref>

